-- UK's financial ombudsman promotes Caroline Wayman to top post 
-- By Matt Scuffham
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 10:18AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 23 (Reuters) - Britain's Financial Ombudsman Service has appointed Caroline Wayman as its new chief executive and chief ombudsman, replacing Natalie Ceeney who stepped down last November to take up a position at HSBC <HSBA.L>.

Wayman is currently the principal ombudsman and legal director and has been with the Financial Ombudsman Service since 2000. She previously worked in the insurance sector.